recompense /ˈrɛkəmˌpɛns/

(recompensing,recompensed,recompenses) 

1. N-UNCOUNT If you are given something, usually money, in recompense , you are given it as a reward or because you have suffered. 奖赏; 补偿 [正式] 

例： He demands no financial recompense for his troubles. 他对遭受到的麻烦没有要求经济补偿。 

2. V-T If you recompense someone for their efforts or their loss, you give them something, usually money, as a payment or reward. 报酬; 赔偿 [正式] 

例： If they succeed in court, they will be fully recompensed for their loss. 如果他们在法庭上胜诉，他们的损失就会得到全额赔偿。

